title.narrative: IMCI AND IMMUNIZATION

description.narrative: By 2017 health facilities and communities have the capacity to implement Integrated Management of Childhood Illness (IMCI) (staff trained and supervised, commodities available, VHVs/CBDs/CBOs trained and supervised) and provide immunization services (staff trained and supervised, cold chain and vaccines management) for all children under five, which contributes to Child Health, Immunization, Maternal And Newborn Health. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2017, the capacities of the Government and relevant stakeholders are strengthened to improve quality, access and utilization of maternal, newborn, child and adolescent health services, including sexual and reproductive health.

description.narrative: The cold chain capacities in 10 provinces were strengthened with installation of cold chain equipment and staff training. Tetanus Toxoid Supplementary Immunisation Activities (TT-SIA) in two high-risks provinces (Madang X Hela) were implemented. An integrated Bottleneck Analysis (BNA) on immunisation services was conducted in Western province. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:20/12/2017
